You are here: SALESFORCE HELP DOCS SERVICE CLOUD Skills Backlog Tab

The Skills Backlog tab is shown only if you have skills-based routing enabled. Keep an eye on your backlog of unassigned work items using the Skills Backlog Summary view. You can see work item types, details, skills, priority, work size, and wait times.

Skills are assigned to work items by PendingServiceRouting. If there aren’t any agents with required skills, then the work item is placed in the backlog.

To drill down and see work items that require specific skills, select one or more skills in the Skills column. The Skill view shows pending work items requiring those skills, along with skills needed, skill level, priority, work size, and waiting time.

Fields for the Omni Supervisor Skills Backlog tab are available only in orgs using skills-based routing for Omni-Channel.
